==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thematic
<hw>The*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/: cf. F.
<ets>th⟦eacute⟧matique</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Gram.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the theme of a word. See <er>Theme</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>, 4.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to a theme, or
subject.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thematic catalogue</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>a
catalogue of musical works which, besides the title and other
particulars, gives in notes the theme, or first few measures, of the
whole work or of its several movements.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Theme</ent>⟦br⟧
